
Bugs:

- Sometimes littlefs2 returns garbage in lfs2_fs_traverse. Probably a bug.

- Sometimes littlefs2 just breaks when creating many files. Not sure why.

- yaffs2 does not work with >=1MiB block sizes for some reason, errors
  with ENOSPC (twisted internally to EINVAL?). Note sure why.

- yaffs2 keeps track of all files (not just opened ones) with a linked-list
  that makes many testing grow O(n^2). This makes many benchmarking
  extremely slow and doesn't trigger an early exit because we ignore CPU
  time.

